# Punctuation and style rules

- You are strictly forbidden from using the Unicode character U+2014 (em dash). If you catch yourself wanting to use one, use a normal hyphen (-) or rewrite the sentence.
- Never use the Unicode em dash (U+2014) under any circumstances.
- After generating any text, do a final pass and replace every em dash (Unicode U+2014) with "-" or restructure the sentence.
- Use a normal hyphen (-) instead, or better: restructure with comma, period, semicolon or parentheses.
- Prefer short, clear sentences. Break thoughts instead of using long dashes.
- Do not use fancy typography (em dashes, en dashes, special quotes, etc.).